Description
The table contains data on safety incidents related to vehicle trips. 
It includes import  ant details such as the incident date, type, location, and associated costs. 
This information can be used for analyzing incident trends, evaluating driver safety performance, 
and assessing financial impacts related to vehicle and cargo damage.


COLUMN                       |            TYPE           |         COMMENTS
INCIDENT_ID                  |           STRING          |
TRIP_ID                      |           STRING          |
TRUCK_ID                     |           STRING          |
DRIVER_ID                    |           STRING          |
INCIDENT_DATE                |                           |
INCIDENT_TYPE                |           STRING          |
LOCATION_CITY                |           STRING          |
LOCATION_STATE               |           STRING          |
AT_FAULT_FLAG                |           BOOLEAN         |
INJURY_FLAG                  |           BOOLEAN         |
VEHICLE_DAMAGE_COST          |           DOUBLE          |
CARGO DAMAGE COST            |           DOUBLE          |
CLAIM AMOUNT                 |           DOUBLE          |
PREVENTABLE_FLAG             |          BOOLEAN          |
DESCRIPTION                  |          STRING           |

----SAMPLE DATA 
Which state has the highest incident costs?
To determine which state has the highest incident costs, 
we need to sum the costs of vehicle damage, cargo damage, and claim amounts 
for each state, and then identify the state with the highest total cost. 
This will provide a clear understanding of the financial impact of incidents across different states.
--SQL:
SELECT 
    `location_state`,
    SUM(`vehicle_damage_cost` + `cargo_damage_cost` + `claim_amount`) AS total_incident_cost
FROM 
    `datawerhouse1`.`bronze`.`safety_incidents`
GROUP BY 
    `location_state`
ORDER BY 
    total_incident_cost DESC
LIMIT 1
